Talk him up!

15:24.300 --> 15:25.834
I got an idea.

15:25.868 --> 15:27.870
Let her live her life.

15:27.903 --> 15:29.539
That's just crazy talk.

15:29.572 --> 15:31.240
It's in your book.

15:31.273 --> 15:32.875
Oh, you're right.

15:37.279 --> 15:39.915
Is it wrong to lust
after a mannequin?

15:42.151 --> 15:42.951
What?

15:42.985 --> 15:44.286
You're busy.

15:44.320 --> 15:45.120
Sorry.

15:45.154 --> 15:45.954
No, no, no.

15:45.988 --> 15:46.855
No, come on...

15:46.889 --> 15:48.057
Come in.

15:48.090 --> 15:49.892
Grab a chair.

15:49.925 --> 15:50.893
Have a seat.

15:54.163 --> 15:56.198
Now, what's the issue?

15:56.231 --> 15:58.635
You know how mannequins
can be super hot?

15:58.668 --> 16:01.303
Is it wrong to think that?

16:01.337 --> 16:03.540
I mean, they're not human.

16:03.573 --> 16:04.940
They're wood.

16:04.973 --> 16:06.875
Most are plastic.

16:06.909 --> 16:08.944
So you get it?

16:08.977 --> 16:09.978
I don't know where
you're shoppin'-

16:10.012 --> 16:11.914
- Oh, they're everywhere.

16:11.947 --> 16:14.950
And at first, I was turning
my eyes away from real girls

16:14.983 --> 16:16.885
and then there they were.

16:16.919 --> 16:18.320
I mean, everywhere.

16:19.556 --> 16:22.592
Well, Blaise, as a teenager,

16:22.625 --> 16:25.294
I imagine you still have lots of

16:26.396 --> 16:28.531
changes going on in your body.

16:28.565 --> 16:30.633
Because I'm born again now?

16:30.667 --> 16:31.468
No.

16:33.102 --> 16:36.038
Have you talked to your
parents about this?

16:36.071 --> 16:37.906
Mannequin lust?

16:37.940 --> 16:39.074
Well, I meant, you know,

16:39.108 --> 16:41.411
becoming a Christian, and
hanging out at church, all that?

16:41.444 --> 16:43.413
They're uber supportive,

16:43.446 --> 16:47.149
and whatever makes me
happy, that's their thing.

16:47.182 --> 16:48.518
Well, Blaise,

16:49.686 --> 16:51.688
you can't have a
meaningful relationship

16:51.721 --> 16:54.524
with those kinda women.

16:54.557 --> 16:57.494
I can't believe I'm
callin' 'em women.

16:57.527 --> 16:58.595
They're nothing!

16:58.628 --> 17:00.397
They're heartless.

17:00.430 --> 17:01.664
They're brainless.

17:01.698 --> 17:02.699
They all are.

17:02.732 --> 17:05.032
So I'm guessing
you're still single?

17:07.169 --> 17:11.708
Can I help you?

17:11.741 --> 17:12.575
Really?

17:13.710 --> 17:15.944
Yeah, I think
that's how it works.

17:15.978 --> 17:18.213
You come into my
office, and I help you.

17:18.247 --> 17:20.949
Do you have a kid
in our program?

17:20.983 --> 17:21.983
No.

17:22.017 --> 17:23.486
No kids, no husband.

17:24.753 --> 17:26.155
That's good.

17:26.188 --> 17:27.122
I don't mean it's good.

17:27.156 --> 17:29.091
I mean, it's not bad either.

17:29.124 --> 17:30.359
I just...

17:30.393 --> 17:31.394
All I mean is,

17:31.428 --> 17:33.996
single people are often single.

17:36.399 --> 17:37.734
You talk for a living, right?

17:42.037 --> 17:43.071
Yikes!

17:43.105 --> 17:45.140
That's a rough first impression.

17:45.174 --> 17:47.042
Oh, don't worry about that.

17:47.075 --> 17:49.712
I got my first impression
of him a long time ago.

17:49.746 --> 17:51.414
You did?

17:51.448 --> 17:54.717
When would that have been
at, a conference, or...

17:54.751 --> 17:57.119
I'm sorry, I'm lost here.

17:57.152 --> 17:59.288
Yeah,
I would say you are,

17:59.321 --> 18:01.691
and you obviously need
help more than I do,

18:01.724 --> 18:04.059
which is why I'm here.

18:04.092 --> 18:06.396
So you're here to volunteer?

18:07.664 --> 18:09.131
If that's the case,

18:09.164 --> 18:10.733
you need to be a church member,

18:10.767 --> 18:14.236
and fill out an
application form.

18:15.472 --> 18:17.440
I am a long-time
church member,

18:17.474 --> 18:18.575
and I can write.

18:18.608 --> 18:21.176
So we're off to a good start.

18:21.210 --> 18:23.245
This is Blaise.

18:23.278 --> 18:24.279
And you are?

18:25.815 --> 18:27.015
Pleased to meet you.

18:27.049 --> 18:28.551
I see how it is.

18:29.419 --> 18:30.252
Do you know Jesus?

18:30.285 --> 18:31.387
He's a new believer.

18:31.421 --> 18:32.622
Yes, I do.

18:32.655 --> 18:34.256
I could climb a
mountain for Jesus!

18:34.289 --> 18:35.792
Who is very enthusiastic.

18:35.825 --> 18:37.159
Seriously, throw me a rope.

18:37.192 --> 18:39.061
Blaise, you are a pickle.

18:39.094 --> 18:39.995
Thank you.

18:40.028 --> 18:42.030
Don't you have a jar
you need to get to?

18:42.064 --> 18:42.765
I was just headed to the mall.

18:42.799 --> 18:43.800
No, no, no, no!

18:43.833 --> 18:44.767
Sit, sit!

18:44.801 --> 18:47.770
Oh, so here's a volunteer
application form

18:47.804 --> 18:50.773
that you'll need
to fill out now.

18:54.844 --> 18:56.713
Sneaky way of getting my name.

18:56.746 --> 18:58.180
This is weird.

18:58.213 --> 18:59.114
Is this flirting?

18:59.147 --> 19:00.550
Unless you wanna back out?

19:00.583 --> 19:02.150
Wait, can you date volunteers?

19:02.184 --> 19:03.520
Why would I wanna back out?

19:03.553 --> 19:05.087
That's like a
church policy, right?

19:05.120 --> 19:07.089
Yes, Blaise, there's a policy.

19:07.122 --> 19:08.591
Is that right?

19:08.625 --> 19:11.093
May I just...

19:11.126 --> 19:13.095
So you're turning me down?

19:13.128 --> 19:15.297
Church policy
dictates that I must.

19:15.330 --> 19:18.701
Well, we are under
grace here, not law.

19:22.271 --> 19:25.073
You just threw away my name.

19:25.107 --> 19:29.144
Okay, so when you figure
it out, give me a call.

19:29.177 --> 19:30.613
Let me know how I can help.

19:30.647 --> 19:35.217
So nice
to meet you, Blaise.

19:43.393 --> 19:44.661
Carla Finney.

19:46.896 --> 19:49.699
Is that Pastor Skip's daughter?

19:50.867 --> 19:52.100
I mean, they both have
the same last name,

19:52.134 --> 19:54.871
so is it?

19:57.907 --> 19:59.442
All right, take
it from the top.

19:59.475 --> 20:00.877
♪ Two, three, four ♪

20:00.910 --> 20:02.879
All right, everybody.

20:02.912 --> 20:05.782
Sing it like you
mean it this time!

20:05.815 --> 20:07.750
What?

20:07.784 --> 20:09.886
It's the first song.

20:09.919 --> 20:11.487
So?

20:11.521 --> 20:14.323
They haven't had a
chance to be insincere yet.

20:14.356 --> 20:16.325
Rocked from out here.

20:16.358 --> 20:18.494
It doesn't rock up here.

20:18.528 --> 20:22.297
Tino, I would like you
to meet my daughter, Carla.

20:36.278 --> 20:37.847
Carla Finney.

20:37.880 --> 20:38.715
- Hi.
- Hi.

20:40.516 --> 20:43.352
♪ Carla Finney ♪

20:43.386 --> 20:46.923
♪ I heard so much about you ♪

20:46.956 --> 20:51.193
♪ It makes me witty and giddy ♪

20:52.562 --> 20:53.463
You know what?

20:53.496 --> 20:55.632
I'm gonna write you a song.

20:55.665 --> 20:57.400
Another one?

20:57.433 --> 20:59.368
Thank you, but that
would be too much.

20:59.402 --> 21:00.202
No, no, I mean it.

21:00.235 --> 21:01.370
No, I mean it too.

21:04.339 --> 21:08.411
♪ Now you're here
from so far away ♪

21:08.444 --> 21:10.947
♪ Moldova ♪

21:10.980 --> 21:12.415
♪ But if you leave ♪

21:12.448 --> 21:17.420
♪ You're gonna
shoot our hearts ♪

21:17.987 --> 21:20.490
♪ With a revolver ♪

21:21.391 --> 21:22.190
Wow!

21:23.593 --> 21:24.527
I know.

21:25.528 --> 21:26.896
I just made that up just now.

21:26.929 --> 21:27.964
Did you?

21:27.997 --> 21:29.932
My whole life is a musical.

21:29.966 --> 21:31.266
Enchanting.

21:31.299 --> 21:32.769
Except for the talking parts,

21:32.802 --> 21:35.672
because it's kind of a
disappointment when I have to talk.

21:35.705 --> 21:37.272
I can see that.

21:37.305 --> 21:37.974
Really?

21:38.007 --> 21:39.609
Yeah.

21:39.642 --> 21:40.810
We get each other.

21:40.843 --> 21:42.310
Oh, you know, dad
and I have to...

21:42.344 --> 21:43.311
There's a...

21:43.345 --> 21:44.947
It was so nice to meet you.

21:44.981 --> 21:46.549
♪ Nice meeting you ♪

21:46.582 --> 21:47.517
Nice to meet you.

21:47.550 --> 21:48.885
♪ I hope to see you again ♪

21:48.918 --> 21:53.321
♪ And baby, oh, I'll call you ♪

21:53.355 --> 21:55.425
Oh, that's
okay, I'll see you around.

21:55.458 --> 21:56.459
All right.

22:02.532 --> 22:03.633
You didn't even try.

22:03.666 --> 22:06.301
You could be his leading lady.

22:06.334 --> 22:08.638
I am happy just
being a bit player.

22:08.671 --> 22:10.305
You won't even go
on one date with him?

22:10.338 --> 22:12.307
That's never gonna happen.

22:12.340 --> 22:13.009
Never say never, honey.

22:13.042 --> 22:14.143
It's an ugly word.

22:14.177 --> 22:16.344
Dad, I didn't come home
for another relationship.

22:16.379 --> 22:17.847
I came home to recover from one.

22:17.880 --> 22:20.516
I know, I'm just
thinking long-term here.

22:20.550 --> 22:22.885
I'm just here on
a round-trip ticket.

22:22.919 --> 22:24.319
What?

22:24.352 --> 22:26.321
I thought you were here to stay?

22:26.354 --> 22:27.289
Maybe.

22:27.322 --> 22:28.356
We'll see.

22:28.391 --> 22:30.393
Ooh, there's Tino's car.

22:30.426 --> 22:31.359
It's new.

22:31.394 --> 22:32.495
It's electric.

22:32.528 --> 22:36.264
Dad, it's a nice car, but
it doesn't change the man.

22:36.298 --> 22:37.166
I just don't want you with

22:37.200 --> 22:39.035
any more of these
crazy, ambitious-types.

22:39.068 --> 22:40.335
Bump.

22:44.741 --> 22:45.942
Tino's ambitious.

22:45.975 --> 22:49.545
Yeah, but he's too
simple to pull it off.

22:51.781 --> 22:54.316
Look, a fellow who
keeps things simple

22:54.349 --> 22:55.350
is not gonna hurt you.

22:55.384 --> 22:56.619
They won't abandon you,

22:56.652 --> 22:59.455
and they're not gonna
take you away from here.

22:59.489 --> 23:02.290
That's funny coming from a
man who leaves professionally.

23:02.324 --> 23:05.027
I was never gone for more
than three months at a time.

23:05.061 --> 23:07.295
You were gone for
nine months, Dad.

23:07.329 --> 23:08.531
Not true.

23:08.564 --> 23:11.501
Technically, those were three
consecutive book tours, right?

23:11.534 --> 23:13.736
Oh, okay, all better.

23:13.770 --> 23:15.872
Come on, I was
home every Sunday.

23:15.905 --> 23:19.442
Ew, technically, you
are here every Sunday.

23:19.475 --> 23:20.777
Ouch.

23:20.810 --> 23:23.412
I know you were making
major life decisions

23:23.446 --> 23:24.380
and I was not there for you,

23:24.413 --> 23:28.350
and I will regret that
for the rest of my life.

23:28.384 --> 23:30.887
It's good to
hear you say that,

23:30.920 --> 23:33.355
'cause I always felt like you
ministered to everyone else

23:33.389 --> 23:34.490
but your own family.

23:34.524 --> 23:36.592
And for that, I am so sorry.

23:36.626 --> 23:38.728
The good news is, I'm
not going anywhere,

23:38.761 --> 23:40.530
and now, neither are you.

23:42.131 --> 23:43.331
Here we are.

23:46.636 --> 23:48.336
Carla, I'm really
glad you're home.

23:48.370 --> 23:49.639
It is so good to see you.

23:49.672 --> 23:51.107
You too.

23:51.140 --> 23:52.909
Oh, and I'll work on trying
to get you a better spot.

23:52.942 --> 23:54.377
Oh, no problem.

23:56.145 --> 23:57.547
I really enjoyed our chat.

23:57.580 --> 23:59.015
Me too.

23:59.048 --> 24:01.584
Will you at least think
about giving Tino a chance?

24:01.617 --> 24:03.351
I don't know, Dad.

24:03.386 --> 24:05.454
Honey, I can't fix all
the things I did wrong

24:05.488 --> 24:06.289
when you were a little girl,

24:06.321 --> 24:08.391
but maybe I can
make it up to you?

24:08.424 --> 24:10.760
All we can do is move forward.

24:10.793 --> 24:11.627
Okay.

24:12.628 --> 24:13.696
No, really.

24:13.729 --> 24:15.398
All we can do is move forward.

24:15.431 --> 24:16.699
The reverse is broken.

24:16.732 --> 24:19.035
I'm gonna need you
to push me back.

24:19.068 --> 24:20.570
You want me to push?

24:20.603 --> 24:22.638
I have to drive.

24:22.672 --> 24:23.472
Yep.

24:23.506 --> 24:24.874
Get around front.

24:24.907 --> 24:26.843
Yeah.

24:26.876 --> 24:28.477
Put your shoulder into it.

24:28.511 --> 24:29.946
It's kinda heavy.

24:30.813 --> 24:32.114
Come on.

24:32.148 --> 24:33.382
Oh.

24:33.416 --> 24:34.116
Hey, babe?

24:34.150 --> 24:35.418
Babe.

24:35.451 --> 24:36.853
Walking through the door.

24:36.886 --> 24:38.454
I'm walking through the
doors as we speak, literally.

24:38.487 --> 24:39.922
Yes, I just walked
through the doors.

24:39.956 --> 24:41.090
As long as I don't

24:41.123 --> 24:42.758
- get held up by some-
- Pastor Guy?

24:42.792 --> 24:43.593
- Good to see you.
- Chad.

24:43.626 --> 24:46.062
Yes, I will...

24:46.095 --> 24:48.397
Yes, Chad, I'll be right up.

24:48.431 --> 24:49.599
Walmart's got nothin'
on you, buddy.

24:49.632 --> 24:50.833
Amateurs.

24:50.867 --> 24:53.069
Hey, I would love to
chat, but I am late.

24:53.102 --> 24:55.171
For your meeting
with Pastor Skip, yeah.

24:55.204 --> 24:57.506
Planning these events
can just be grueling.

24:57.540 --> 24:59.075
Yeah, they can.

24:59.108 --> 25:01.577
Each stunt having to be
bigger and better than the last.

25:01.611 --> 25:02.511
Oh, stunts.

25:02.545 --> 25:03.546
Heard you met with Carla?

25:03.579 --> 25:04.914
Wow.

25:04.947 --> 25:06.048
Wow what?

25:06.082 --> 25:08.184
Well, I just think you
two could make a great team.

25:08.217 --> 25:09.819
I mean, I'm focused
on the youth group.

25:09.852 --> 25:11.053
Nah, you're right,

25:11.087 --> 25:12.154
she'd probably just
be a distraction.

25:16.993 --> 25:19.161
I guess I could use some help?

25:19.195 --> 25:21.697
What a great idea.

25:21.731 --> 25:23.532
You should keep
going, you're late.

25:23.566 --> 25:24.867
Hey, thanks, Chad.

25:35.511 --> 25:39.515
There he is.

25:42.585 --> 25:43.686
I did it!

25:43.719 --> 25:45.087
I took my nap!

25:45.121 --> 25:46.455
Wham!

25:46.489 --> 25:47.490
It came to me.

25:47.523 --> 25:50.893
Something, really, really
big for Good Friday.

25:50.927 --> 25:52.528
Big.

25:52.561 --> 25:53.596
Uh-oh.

25:54.563 --> 25:57.967
This is gonna be our
most daring event ever.

25:58.000 --> 26:00.469
This year, for Good Friday,

26:00.503 --> 26:02.505
we are gonna have a crucifixion.

26:03.673 --> 26:05.508
You mean, a
passion play, right?

26:05.541 --> 26:08.544
Oh, no, no, no, an
actual crucifixion.

26:08.577 --> 26:12.214
Like they do in Mexico
and the Philippines?

26:12.248 --> 26:13.983
Wait.

26:14.016 --> 26:15.985
You knew about that?

26:16.018 --> 26:17.253
Why didn't you tell me?

26:17.286 --> 26:20.056
'Cause it's a
mockery of the Gospel.

26:20.089 --> 26:21.824
No, it's an homage.

26:22.959 --> 26:24.527
It's impactful.

26:24.560 --> 26:27.530
And we are bringin'
it to Sand Hills.

26:27.563 --> 26:31.534
You're gonna crucify
a human in church?

26:31.567 --> 26:32.501
Yes.

26:32.535 --> 26:36.605
This will cement us as
the cutting edge church.

26:36.639 --> 26:38.741
Okay, Skip, I realize
you can't see this,

26:38.774 --> 26:40.943
because you're crazy,

26:40.977 --> 26:43.980
but no one is going
to be okay with this.

26:44.013 --> 26:45.247
Everybody's okay with it.

26:45.281 --> 26:47.116
The board already approved it,

26:47.149 --> 26:51.287
and they approved shooting
confetti during the altar call.

26:51.320 --> 26:53.556
How does this involve me?

26:55.992 --> 26:58.027
I wanna give you the honor

26:58.060 --> 27:02.665
of being the first man
crucified in an American church.

27:12.875 --> 27:15.911
♪ Whoa ♪

27:15.945 --> 27:18.114
♪ Oh, man ♪

27:20.983 --> 27:22.618
♪ Whoa ♪

27:24.020 --> 27:26.255
♪ Oh, yeah ♪

27:30.226 --> 27:31.594
I'm not sure how to say this,

27:31.627 --> 27:33.195
but you are insane!

27:38.000 --> 27:40.036
I have no role in this!

27:40.069 --> 27:41.871
It'll
be perfectly safe.

27:41.904 --> 27:44.273
That's the reason
Dr. Knott is here.

27:44.306 --> 27:45.274
You see, Guy,

27:45.307 --> 27:47.576
it wasn't the nails that
actually killed people.

27:47.610 --> 27:50.179
Most died by asphyxiation.

27:50.212 --> 27:51.013
See?

27:51.047 --> 27:52.281
Science.

27:52.314 --> 27:55.351
And no one in Mexico
has died from this.

27:55.385 --> 27:57.620
As far as we know.

27:57.653 --> 28:00.056
By placing the nails through
your palms in the right place,

28:00.089 --> 28:03.092
we hope to avoid
major nerve damage.

28:04.727 --> 28:06.729
Nothing is 100%.

28:06.762 --> 28:08.664
You'll have to sign
a waiver, of course,

28:08.697 --> 28:09.865
to protect the church.

28:09.899 --> 28:11.233
And one for me too.

28:11.267 --> 28:12.101
Sure.

28:13.869 --> 28:15.271
All right!

28:15.304 --> 28:17.673
Good meeting, everyone.

28:17.706 --> 28:19.341
Guy, Guy, wait, wait!

28:19.375 --> 28:20.176
Where are you going?

28:20.209 --> 28:21.310
Come on!

28:21.343 --> 28:23.345
You're the eighth person on
the staff to turn us down.

28:23.380 --> 28:25.347
Even Tino said no.

28:25.382 --> 28:26.849
Turns out, he's a bleeder.

28:26.882 --> 28:28.617
He doesn't have
enough platelets.

28:28.651 --> 28:30.886
He can't form scabs.

28:30.920 --> 28:32.955
Think about this, Guy.

28:32.988 --> 28:34.890
This is gonna be huge,

28:34.924 --> 28:37.626
bigger than anything
we've ever done,

28:37.660 --> 28:40.729
National headlines,
monster book sales.

28:40.763 --> 28:44.967
This is what I'm
trying to get away from.

28:45.000 --> 28:46.168
Gimmicks!

28:46.202 --> 28:48.304
You call it gimmicks,

28:48.337 --> 28:51.073
I call it souls in the seats.

28:51.107 --> 28:54.643
You know, Skip I think
the Gospel's enough.

29:00.349 --> 29:02.685
I did not see that coming.

29:07.123 --> 29:07.923
- Great seeing you too.
- Let me know if you

29:07.957 --> 29:09.191
need anymore help.

29:09.225 --> 29:10.693
- Mm-hmm.
- Tell me you stopped him?

29:10.726 --> 29:12.828
Stop Pastor Finney, Carla?

29:12.862 --> 29:14.096
Carla Finney.

29:14.130 --> 29:15.898
I get it, you
know who I am now.

29:15.931 --> 29:18.968
I'm sorry I didn't recognize
you, but you've aged.

29:19.001 --> 29:20.437
Thanks?

29:20.470 --> 29:22.138
That's what happens when
you've been gone for 10 years.

29:22.171 --> 29:25.241
No, you look way better
than a lot of women your age.

29:25.274 --> 29:27.009
